  "prompt": "Is Turkey considered to be more in Asia or in Europe?",
  "response": "Turkey is considered a transcontinental country, with territory spanning both Asia and Europe. The majority of Turkey's landmass, approximately 97%, lies in Asia, while the remaining 3%, including the historically significant region of Eastern Thrace, is located in Europe. The Bosporus Strait acts as a natural boundary, separating the Asian part from the European part of Turkey. Therefore, Turkey is often viewed as more predominantly Asian, but its strategic location and cultural connections make it an integral part of both continents.",
